r>0
r\leq x\leq y
\implies
\ln y - \ln x \leq \frac{y-x}{r}
\ln x
(0,\infty)
0<r\leq x \leq y
[x,y]\subset(0,\infty)
c\in(x,y)
f'(c)=\frac{f(y)-f(x)}{y-x}
\frac{1}{c}=\frac{\ln y - \ln x}{y-x}
\frac{y-x}{c}=\ln y - \ln x
r\leq x \leq y
c\in(x,y)
r\leq c
\frac{y-x}{c}\leq\frac{y-x}{r}
\frac{y-x}{r}\geq \ln y - \ln x
